  ShellPort — Help
  ================

  Drop your own help.md (or help.txt) in the project root and it
  shows up in this panel. Useful for things you'd otherwise forget,
  like which .bat to double-click before leaving the house.

  Recommended sections:

    1. URL + login          — what to type, what to expect
    2. The targets          — what each one is for
    3. Enable / disable     — which scripts to run, which to close
    4. Troubleshooting      — common red dots and how to fix them

  This file is gitignored when named "help.md", so it's safe to
  put internal IPs / aliases / personal hints in it. Only the
  *.example template is committed.
